        public static java.lang.Class getObjectClass(java.lang.Class clazz)
        Deprecated. 
        Primitive types have two classes in java. The primitive one (ie. int.class) and the Object one (ie. Integer.class). This takes the Object one (ie. int.class) and returns the primitive one (ie. Integer.class)
        Parameters:
        clazz - The primitive class to get the Object version
        Returns:
        The Object version, or null if there isn't one
        See Also:
        getPrimitiveClass(Class)
